Package org.jsonurl

Provides the base interfaces, classes, and exceptions needed to parse the JSON→URL grammar.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BigMathProvider
    Provides an instance of MathContext and related content.
    ExceptionProvider
    An instance of this interface can create parse, limit, and syntax exceptions with parser-specific position information.
    JsonUrlLimits
    JSON→URL text parse limits.
    JsonUrlLimits.Builder
    JSON→URL text limit builder.
    JsonUrlOptionable
    An instance of this interface is something that can provide JsonUrlOptions.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BigMath
    A simple BigMathProvider implementation.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BigMathProvider.BigIntegerOverflow
    Enumeration of BigInteger overflow operations.
    CompositeType
    An enumeration of JSON→URL composite types.
    JsonUrlOption
    An enumeration of JSON→URL options available to both parsing and serialization.
    LimitException.Message
    Enumeration of messages.
    SyntaxException.Message
    Enumeration of messages.
    ValueType
    An enumeration of JSON→URL value types.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    LimitException
    A exception that occurs when a limit is exceeded.
    ParseException
    An exception that occurs while parsing JSON→URL text.
    SyntaxException
    A syntax error in JSON→URL text.
